<div id="pressRelease">
  <h3>CES 2018 Launches Gary’s Book Club Call for Authors</h3>
  <h4>June 30 Deadline</h4>
  <em>Arlington, VA&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;04/24/2017</em>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;The Consumer Technology Association (CTA) today announced its call for author proposals <a href="http://www.ces.tech/Events-Programs/Garys-Book-Club">to join Gary&rsquo;s Book Club</a>, presented by Barnes &amp; Noble, at CES&reg; 2018. Participating authors will partake in book signings on site, promote their books to CES attendees and engage in lively discussions on the Consumer Technology Stage when CES returns to Las Vegas Jan. 9-12, 2018. Authors interested in participating in Gary&rsquo;s Book Club for CES 2018 can apply at&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ces.tech/Events-Programs/Garys-Book-Club">CES.tech</a>. Applications will be accepted through June 30.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
Authors eligible to participate in Gary&rsquo;s Book Club must have a book published between January 2017 and January 2018 that is related to technology, innovation and/or tech innovation public policy. There is no charge for authors to participate in the program.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
&ldquo;Our book club offers a stage for authors to interact with CES attendees, discuss their work and explore topics that are truly front and center in the technology industry,&rdquo; said Gary Shapiro, president and CEO, CTA, and best-selling author of CTA&rsquo;s&nbsp;<em>Ninja Innovation: The Ten Killer Strategies of the World&rsquo;s Most Successful Businesses</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>The Comeback: How Innovation will Restore the American Dream.&nbsp;</em>&ldquo;We encourage authors to join the fifth year of the book club to share their work and visions at CES 2018.&rdquo;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
Learn more about the <a href="http://www.ces.tech/Events-Programs/Garys-Book-Club#authors" title="11 esteemed authors">11 esteemed authors</a> Gary&#39;s Book Club brought to CES 2017&#39;s <a href="http://www.ces.tech/Events-Programs/Garys-Book-Club#videos" title="CTA Stage in the Grand Lobby">CTA Stage in the Grand Lobby</a>.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.ces.tech/Events-Programs/Garys-Book-Club"><img alt="" src="https://prod1.cta.tech/CTA/media/Other/gbc_button.JPG" style="vertical-align: middle;" /></a><br />
<br />
<strong>High-definition video b-roll from CES is available for easy download on <a href="http://www.cesbroll.com/">CESbroll.com</a></strong><br />
